n}\n\n.navbar a {\n  color: #000000;\n  text-decoration: none;\n  margin-right: 10px;\n}\n```\nThis CSS template uses Arial and Times New Roman as the font family, which were commonly used in the early days of the web. The font size is set to 14px, which is also typical of web pages from that era. The background color is set to white, which was a common choice for web pages at that time, and the text alignment is centered. The headings (h1, h2, h3) use the Times New Roman font and the links (a) are blue and underlined with a red color on hover. The images are given a 1px solid black border.\n\nI\'ve also added a .container class which is set to 800px width and centered with margin auto, it helps to contain all the contents in the website.\nAnd a .navbar class is added for navigation bar with a light gray background color and some padding and text alignment.\n\nPlease note that this is just a basic template, you can always add more css styles and customize it to your liking.\n<|im_end|>\n<|im_start|>assistant\n', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=0, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=100, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None, extra_args=None), prompt_token_ids: None, prompt_embeds shape: None, lora_request: None, prompt_adapter_request: None.
